text: Chittobochiah Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Catalpa Creek. A variant transliteration is "Ittobechi Creek". The name Ittobechi is derived from the Choctaw language, and it's purported to mean "one that causes fighting". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lowndes County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Oktibbeha County, Mississippi
title: Chittobochiah Creek
